<br>
We had four mages in the guild, and we all needed this *explective* mob, so we all decided to start here, after all, after quill the rest seems a tad easier. <br>
<br>
We had two to three groups each time we spawned her. It just so happened that once they were all of the AE classes, and ONE bard, and a few trackers. So the bard pulled all the moving mobs he could round up, in the neighborhood of &quot;I just can't count them all&quot; and pulled them to the hillside facing paw. The groups AEed the living snot out of them. About five pulls later two of the trackers went ape and ran towards that valley between the two hills, in the direction of KFC. They then shouted for the mages to get over there NOW. She dropped the cloak, I lost the roll.<br>
<br>
We did that until she spawned again,  Cloak again, I rolled a 99 and won. It was not that long with the AE groups, maybe about 30 minutes, maybe less.<br>
<br>
I HIGHLY recommend this. A gm showed up to deal with a spire camp issue and I asked if the AE spawn of Quill was approved and she said &quot;as long as you don't pull something that someone already has attacked I don't cared if you get the whole zone in an AE&quot;. <br>
<br>
I tried to do a single group spawn and it took FIVE hours. So I recommend that you get a &quot;fun guild picknic&quot; summon up a few Bristlebanes bundles and make it into a party.<br>
